no (the racks were temporarily placed in the costco model so i can scale them correctly as well as compare their size relative to the building itself). the only things that were modeled in-engine were the terrain meshes featured in the forest and the beach level, along with the test park which is made of primitives/test blocks. eveything else is made piece by piece in blunder then placed together in the engine as seperate models (quarterpipes, concrete pads, general structures like the forest warehouse itself, etc). in the future, i'll probably model small parts of terrain and such in blender, such as the hills of a park or urban obsticales. pls feel free to share blunder advice if you have great tips on modeling buildings, environments, etc.
